modName: TES5Edit Script - Find Mod Shared Cells
summary: Compiles list of shared cells between files, and outputs it to the log and a "SharedCells.txt" file next to your xEdit executable.
descriptionHtml:
[b]Description:
[/b]Compiles list of shared cells between files, and outputs it to the log and a "SharedCells.txt" file next to your TES5Edit executable.

[b]Installation: [/b]
Simply move the "SharedCells.pas" file into the "Edit Scripts" folder in your TES5Edit directory.

[b]Pre-Req:[/b]
This file MUST be in your "Edit Scripts" folder, and you must have loaded Skyrim.esm into TES5Edit (Skyrim.esm is automatically loaded with anything that has it as a Master)

[b]Running:
[/b]Choose one of the below:
[list=1]
[*]Use the Hotkey "Alt+C" ("C" for "Cell"!)

[*]Right-Click anything, select "Apply Script", then select "SharedCells" in the drop-down.  Press "OK".

[/list]
[b]Details:[/b]
Allows you to pick any of your loaded files, and then compiles a list of cells per each collided mod, organized by mod and Worldspace.
It then outputs this to a textfile, as well as printing this to the log.

[b]To-Do:[/b]
If someone wants me to expand on this or has an idea to make it better, I'm willing to work on that.
I may add a GUI to better view results if a couple people would find that helpful.
